### ============================================================
### AUTH — OTP Login, Profile Setup, Token Refresh, Logout
### Base URL: http://localhost:8000
###
### HOW THE AUTO-CHAIN WORKS (VS Code REST Client extension):
###   1. Run "Send OTP"       → creates OTP in DB
###   2. Run "Dev — Fetch OTP" → reads OTP from DB, captured as {{devOtp.response.body.otp}}
###   3. Run "Verify OTP"     → uses the captured OTP automatically, returns tokens
###   4. Run any auth'd request → uses {{verifyOtp.response.body.access_token}} automatically
###
### Run each ### block top-to-bottom. No copy-pasting needed.
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@phone = +966501234567
@deviceId = device-test-001


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 1 — SEND OTP
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### [SUCCESS] Send OTP — triggers OTP creation (stored in DB, not sent via SMS in dev)
# @name sendOtp
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone_number": "{{phone}}"
}


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 2 — FETCH OTP (dev endpoint, only works when DEBUG=true)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### [DEV] Fetch OTP from DB — returns the raw OTP for testing
# @name devOtp
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/dev/otp?phone_number={{phone}}


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 3 — VERIFY OTP  (auto-uses OTP from step 2)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### [SUCCESS] Verify OTP — uses OTP captured from devOtp response
# @name verifyOtp
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone_number": "{{phone}}",
  "otp": "{{devOtp.response.body.otp}}",
  "device_id": "{{deviceId}}"
}


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# STEP 4 — COMPLETE PROFILE (only needed if verifyOtp returns needs_profile: true)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### [SUCCESS] Complete Profile — first-time user registration
# @name completeProfile
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/complete-profile
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone_number": "{{phone}}",
  "name": "Ahmed Al-Otaibi",
  "email": "ahmed@example.com",
  "date_of_birth": "1995-06-15",
  "timezone": "Asia/Riyadh",
  "role": "Customer"
}


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# FROM HERE — all requests use tokens auto-captured from verifyOtp
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### [SUCCESS] Get Current User — token from verifyOtp
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{verifyOtp.response.body.access_token}}

###

### [SUCCESS] Update Profile — token from verifyOtp
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{verifyOtp.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ahmed Al-Otaibi",
  "email": "ahmed.updated@example.com",
  "date_of_birth": "1995-06-15",
  "timezone": "Asia/Riyadh"
}

###

### [SUCCESS] Update Timezone
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/timezone
Authorization: Bearer {{verifyOtp.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "timezone": "Asia/Riyadh"
}

###

### [SUCCESS] Update Push Token (FCM/APNs)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/push-token
Authorization: Bearer {{verifyOtp.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "push_token": "fcm_token_abc123xyz789"
}

###

### [SUCCESS] Refresh Token — get new access token using refresh token from verifyOtp
# @name refreshToken
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "{{verifyOtp.response.body.refresh_token}}"
}

###

### [SUCCESS] Logout — revoke refresh token
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "{{verifyOtp.response.body.refresh_token}}"
}


# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# SECURITY / FAILURE TESTS
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

### [FAIL — Security] Get Current User — no token (401 Unauthorized)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

###

### [FAIL — Security] Get Current User — forged JWT (401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiI5OTk5OTkiLCJyb2xlIjoiQWRtaW4ifQ.FAKESIGNATURE

###

### [FAIL — Security] Verify OTP — wrong OTP (400 Invalid OTP)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone_number": "{{phone}}",
  "otp": "000000",
  "device_id": "{{deviceId}}"
}

###

### [FAIL — Security] Verify OTP — non-existent phone number (400 User not found)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone_number": "+966500000000",
  "otp": "123456",
  "device_id": "device-abc"
}

###

### [FAIL — Rate Limit] Send OTP — 4th request triggers 429 Too Many Requests
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone_number": "{{phone}}"
}

###

### [FAIL — Validation] Complete Profile — underage user (400)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/complete-profile
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "phone_number": "{{phone}}",
  "name": "Young User",
  "email": "young@example.com",
  "date_of_birth": "2015-01-01",
  "timezone": "Asia/Riyadh",
  "role": "Customer"
}

###

### [FAIL — Security] Dev OTP endpoint — disabled when DEBUG=false (404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/dev/otp?phone_number={{phone}}

###

### [FAIL — Security] Refresh Token — using access token as refresh token (401)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refresh_token": "{{verifyOtp.response.body.access_token}}"
}

###

### [FAIL — Validation] Update Profile — name too short (400)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{verifyOtp.response.body.access_token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "A",
  "email": "ahmed@example.com",
  "date_of_birth": "1995-06-15"
}
